<span id="Description"></span>
==Beschreibung==

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
The [[Image:Cables_LayersExtended.svg|24px]] [[Cables_LayersExtended|Layers Extended]] are a predefined set of layers, each of which is an extended version of a [[Draft_Layer|Draft Layer]]. The extended layer in addition to the standard properties of a '''Draft Layer''', allows to define the color and size of the points of elements belonging to the layer. Each extended layer has also '''Auto Member Type''' property which is designed to automatically collect layer elements.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
Extended layers were created to make it easier to organize [[Cables_WireFlex|WireFlex]] lines, [[Cables_SupportLine|SupportLines]], [[Cables_SupportPoint|SupportPoints]], [[Cables_SnapLines|SnapLines]], [[Cables_CableTerminal|CableTerminals]]. These layers allow you to quickly and easily assign ungrouped objects of a specific type to the appropriate layer, and then hide or show them, as well as apply bulk changes to their view properties.
</div>

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
Simply recompute the selected layer (e.g. by right clicking it and selecting '''Recompute Object'''), and all ungrouped elements of the selected type will be assigned to it.
</div>

<span id="Usage"></span>
==Anwendung==

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
# Create default set of extended layers by one of these methods:
#* Press the {{Button|[[Image:Cables_LayersExtended.svg|16px]] [[Cables_LayersExtended|Layers Extended]]}} button.
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|Cable Support → [[Image:Cables_LayersExtended.svg|16px]] Layers Extended}} option from the menu.
#* Right-click in the [[Tree_View|Tree View]] or the [[3D_View|3D View]] and select the {{MenuCommand|Cable Support → [[Image:Cables_LayersExtended.svg|16px]] Layers Extended}} option from the context menu.
</div>

<span id="Notes"></span>
==Hinweise==

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* The default layer with '''Auto Member Type''' property set to {{Value|None}} can serve as template for creation other extended layers.
* It is possible to use more than one layer with the same '''Auto Member Type''' property by changing it manually.
* If you run the '''LayersExtended''' command again, it will generate layers for all possible '''Auto Member Type''' types that have not yet been created, plus one additional layer with {{Value|None}} '''Auto Member Type'''.
</div>

<span id="Properties"></span>
==Eigenschaften==

Siehe auch: [[Property_View/de|Eigenschaften-Ansicht]].

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
A '''Layer Extended''' object is derived from a [[Draft_Layer|Draft Layer]] and inherits all its properties. Layer Extended has also the following additional properties:
</div>

<span id="Data"></span>
===Daten===

{{TitleProperty|Layer}}

<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr">
* {{PropertyData|Auto Member Type|Enumeration}}: specifies the type of automatic member of this layer. When layer is recomputed it automatically includes all objects of selected type which were not assigned to any other layer. Possible values: {{Value|None}}, {{Value|WireFlex}}, {{Value|SupportLines}}, {{Value|ExtSnapLines}}, {{Value|CableTerminal}}. When {{Value|None}} is selected the Auto Member Type becomes inactive.
</div>

<span id="View"></span>
===Ansicht===

{{TitleProperty|Layer}}

* {{PropertyData/de|Point Color|Color}}: Legt die Punktfarbe der Ebene fest.
* {{PropertyData/de|Point Size|Float}}: Legt die Punktgröße der Ebene fest.


